de.tinloaf.intervaltree

Class IntervalTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>,I extends HasInterval<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.tinloaf.intervaltree.IntervalTree<E,I>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - Data type of the interval borders. This can be anything that is comparable to itself.
    I - Entry data type. This must implement HasInterval, and the methods implemented must return the interval of the entry

    public class IntervalTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>,I extends HasInterval<E>>
extends java.lang.Object
    An Interval Tree implementation based on a Red-Black-Tree. Supports insertion, deletion, lookups and multiple entries per interval. Please note that this data structure is not static and not concurrency-safe.
    Author:
    Lukas Barth
